Load Image:The image input

This lora is trained to enhance high resolution details while faithfully preserving all subtle features of the original image. Therefore, the subject of the image should have basic clarity, and excessive blurriness will be considered out focus and maintained blur. Similarly, flaws in the image, such as noticeable noise, will not be fixed and will still faithfully high resolution.

Output Size:
The long side of output image.
Excessive size may cause the image to become blurry, it is recommended not to exceed 4k.
24GB of VRAM can approximately run images with a total pixel size of 12M at once, please convert according to the image ratio.
If there is Out of VRAM, please lower this value or activate the `Image Batch to List` node before the `VAE encoder` node for single batch inference.
